# Development Workflow

## Available Scripts
Based on [package.json](mdc:package.json), the following scripts are available:

### Development
- `bun run dev` - Start development server with Vite
- `bun run preview` - Preview production build locally

### Building
- `bun run build` - Build for production (TypeScript compilation + Vite build)

### Code Quality
- `bun run lint` - Run ESLint to check code quality
- `bun run format:check` - Check code formatting with Prettier
- `bun run format` - Format code with Prettier
- `bun run knip` - Detect unused dependencies and exports

## Development Guidelines

### Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new code
- Follow ESLint rules defined in [eslint.config.js](mdc:eslint.config.js)
- Use Prettier for consistent formatting (config in [.prettierrc](mdc:.prettierrc))
- Import sorting is handled by `@trivago/prettier-plugin-sort-imports`

### Component Development
- Use ShadCN UI components from [src/components/](mdc:src/components)
- Follow the component structure in [components.json](mdc:components.json)
- Use Radix UI primitives for accessibility
- Style with Tailwind CSS classes

### State Management
- Use Zustand stores in [src/stores/](mdc:src/stores) for global state
- Use TanStack Query for server state management
- Use React Hook Form with Zod validation for forms

### Routing
- Define routes in [src/routes/](mdc:src/routes) using TanStack Router
- Route tree is auto-generated in [src/routeTree.gen.ts](mdc:src/routeTree.gen.ts)

